# Tic-Tac-Toe AI

## Project Overview

This project implements an **AI-powered Tic-Tac-Toe game** where a human player competes against an intelligent computer opponent. The AI uses the **Minimax algorithm**, a well-known decision-making algorithm in game theory, to determine the best possible move.

The goal of the AI is to analyze all possible game states and select the optimal move, making it **unbeatable when implemented correctly**.

This project helps in understanding **Artificial Intelligence concepts such as game theory, search algorithms, and decision-making strategies**.

---

## Objectives

* Understand the concept of **game-playing AI**
* Implement the **Minimax algorithm**
* Learn how recursive search algorithms work
* Build a human vs AI game using Python
* Understand decision-making in adversarial environments

---

## Features

* Human vs Computer gameplay
* AI opponent using **Minimax algorithm**
* Interactive command-line interface
* Automatic win/draw detection
