## Installation and Setup

### Step 1: Install Python

Make sure Python is installed on your system.

Check Python installation:

```
python --version
```

### Step 2: Download or Clone the Project

Download the project folder or clone the repository.

### Step 3: Navigate to the Project Folder

```
cd tic_tac_toe_ai
```

### Step 4: Run the Program

```
python tic_tac_toe_ai.py
```

---

## Example Gameplay

```
Tic Tac Toe AI
You are X | AI is O

  |   |
--+---+--
  |   |
--+---+--
  |   |

Enter position (1-9): 5
```

The AI will automatically calculate its move and update the board.

---

## Minimax Algorithm Explanation

The **Minimax algorithm** is used to simulate all possible game outcomes and choose the move that maximizes the AI’s chance of winning while minimizing the player's chance.

Possible scores assigned by the AI:

| Game Result | Score |
| ----------- | ----- |
| AI Wins     | +1    |
| Human Wins  | -1    |
| Draw        | 0     |

The AI recursively explores every possible move and selects the move with the **best possible score**.

